Program: The History Hour
Title: Strikers in Saris
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3cswqmq
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 22 Jan 2019
How South Asian women led thousands of UK workers in an industrial dispute in the late 1970s, plus Dr Crippen's alleged gruesome crime, Judy Garland's emotional last performances, the 'miracle waters' in Mexico and excitement over a whale in London's River Thames. (PHOTO: Jayaben Desai, leader of the Grunwick strike committee holding placard 1977 Credit: Getty images) Show less